FRONTLINE ROADS v0.32.11 FINAL AUDIT

Scope
- Remove periodic rendering and state-clone stalls on mobile standard quality
- Keep the simulation and UI state separation intact
- Increase actual enemy population and launch density by civilization level
- Preserve civilization level 0 wave size, timing and former 220-enemy ceiling

Rendering corrections
- Added an independently invalidated combat canvas layer
- Reuses the completed combat layer while simulation state and camera are unchanged
- Consolidated enemy position, road-pressure and lane-distribution scans
- Batched standard/minimal enemy fills by normal/slowed state
- Suppressed per-enemy outer rings above 180 visible enemies
- Limited standard enemy health bars to 20, or 12 in dense scenes
- Preserved full-quality individual glow and radar response

State and scheduling corrections
- Added detached UI snapshots that cache the unchanged road graph
- Periodic HUD refresh shares one UI snapshot across all panels
- Automatic survey polling is throttled to 30 seconds
- No survey facility means no full state transaction or graph clone
- Manual survey remains immediate

Simulation corrections
- Region anchors are built once per assignment sweep
- Region distance uses squared values
- First regional step reuses the existing combat spatial index
- Empty activity regions skip combat-system updates
- Threat ranking retains the top eight candidates without sorting the full enemy set

Enemy density
- Civilization 0: cap 220, wave x1.00, interval x1.00, departure 8.0s
- Civilization 1: cap 320, wave x1.55, interval x0.86, departure 6.0s
- Civilization 2: cap 440, wave x2.25, interval x0.70, departure 4.5s
- Civilization 3: cap 580, wave x3.25, interval x0.56, departure 3.2s
- Civilization 4: cap 720, wave x4.50, interval x0.44, departure 2.4s
- Civilization generation grace uses the preceding density tier
- Enemy-base guard waves retain their fixed composition

Performance evidence
- Standard direct combat draw operations reduced 45.5% at 220 enemies
- Standard direct combat draw operations reduced 60.1% at 500 enemies
- Standard direct combat draw operations reduced 61.6% at 720 enemies
- Minimal direct combat draw operations reduced 50.8% to 63.9%
- Forty UI refresh snapshots on a 2025-node / 3960-edge graph: median 958.861ms -> 0.623ms after cached graph warm-up
- Synthetic 720-enemy, eight-base, five-minute 0.25s-step stress state remained bounded and finite

